[
  {
    "id": "PSA.77.1",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 77,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "[To the chief Musician, to Jeduthun, A Psalm of Asaph.] I cried unto God with my voice, {even} unto God with my voice; and he gave ear unto me. {of: or, for}",
    "hash": "b3eceda770432e9aef58532957e5d76c609e73028f53a13dc9db4bca946f25f6"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.77.2",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 77,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "In the day of my trouble I sought the Lord: my sore ran in the night, and ceased not: my soul refused to be comforted. {sore: Heb. hand}",
    "hash": "c5172736765c4a17cf504c1bd47758a6de0cbfe2311eaa077367d2d28271fd1b"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.77.3",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 77,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "I remembered God, and was troubled: I complained, and my spirit was overwhelmed. Selah.",
    "hash": "6aa8bc8c30d8d4910652a2e809a8a9b2d97654421119692a86e5c6aaba750185"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.77.4",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 77,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Thou holdest mine eyes waking: I am so troubled that I cannot speak.",
    "hash": "bd81b5005da50c2b09a2dcce395c2450f2bb77c18502965f834cb3d54b061691"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.77.5",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 77,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "I have considered the days of old, the years of ancient times.",
    "hash": "1dd4ec70ac8b296c029a79a6ce32c11a96847cf34ff3c0abdd2f1888fc21a033"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.77.6",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 77,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "I call to remembrance my song in the night: I commune with mine own heart: and my spirit made diligent search.",
    "hash": "a1869a3658d64e692242f9acda31df1970cf24cb07c53e9d0da229f838508cce"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.77.7",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 77,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Will the Lord cast off for ever? and will he be favourable no more?",
    "hash": "79dd617a0721a0dae0f2f1e928733532a5b7375f416d6bb5bfdd0dc7b11b2ab3"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.77.8",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 77,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "Is his mercy clean gone for ever? doth {his} promise fail for evermore? {for evermore: Heb. to generation and generation?}",
    "hash": "32821c30621b9149ac43895454eca64de45302477b31fdd8cb17f831a3ce81c2"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.77.9",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 77,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "Hath God forgotten to be gracious? hath he in anger shut up his tender mercies? Selah.",
    "hash": "5a7e88d0c0e8ffdda53c9311a42dcc3f2cd3dc775f277630b6990bf42d2d857b"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.77.10",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 77,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "And I said, This {is} my infirmity: {but I will remember} the years of the right hand of the most High.",
    "hash": "8fbffd10c80daceec3df1bb0cfb784b83804fc6713bc7ba29ea7f8d030d75dfd"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.77.11",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 77,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "I will remember the works of the LORD: surely I will remember thy wonders of old.",
    "hash": "dabf5425e33ec7b269dbafe0d956db376839df89a65359982b0b5ca1c61418a5"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.77.12",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 77,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "I will meditate also of all thy work, and talk of thy doings.",
    "hash": "16209c8ae3ea7cee39442cb14eb47294105c4810891ac8dd4ecd4dc02528bb5e"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.77.13",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 77,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Thy way, O God, {is} in the sanctuary: who {is so} great a God as {our} God?",
    "hash": "6e9a0315fcff39046fc0e58fad6a2cbbcc73bfe0bdfce59e136c28477b9f4e19"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.77.14",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 77,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "Thou {art} the God that doest wonders: thou hast declared thy strength among the people.",
    "hash": "364ebe30010234e3a201fd5558fad5f28e6da44c26af1d24aced969942c4887d"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.77.15",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 77,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "Thou hast with {thine} arm redeemed thy people, the sons of Jacob and Joseph. Selah.",
    "hash": "386a70ae87b01b9852406fe1966e54c7eb76880ddf7fc291897a0a28ce6f48e7"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.77.16",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 77,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "The waters saw thee, O God, the waters saw thee; they were afraid: the depths also were troubled.",
    "hash": "a4ae87f4c2f906e10a0c89735758cad86d58244644c84484f5d2e7069202bef3"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.77.17",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 77,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "The clouds poured out water: the skies sent out a sound: thine arrows also went abroad. {poured...: Heb. were poured forth with water}",
    "hash": "f850c0f439436f3952dd11d71061d98ae6277268be789ae39e7928efad8cb3a4"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.77.18",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 77,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "The voice of thy thunder {was} in the heaven: the lightnings lightened the world: the earth trembled and shook.",
    "hash": "1f5b8b6457a97eb2db5afbd967b6886f681ce52e7dffe65f0f3d53ce85271156"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.77.19",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 77,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Thy way {is} in the sea, and thy path in the great waters, and thy footsteps are not known.",
    "hash": "ab1a979bc8d8638e9615f2420295eba8018867b991c037bfcab588eaf85be255"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.77.20",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 77,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "Thou leddest thy people like a flock by the hand of Moses and Aaron.",
    "hash": "099a1d0c615c012041f10518f0079cc393048555f0cc86605ded156f0adadc3b"
  }
]